Python Statement
Python statement is commonly used to write value, compute a value , assign a value to a varible,
call a function.

x = 4
y = 3
print(x + y)
... the first statement assigns number 4 to the x variable
...The second statement assigns number 3 to the y variable
...The third statement print the addition of a x and y.


Multiple Statement in one line
you can write multiple statement in a single line of code.
Simple separate the statement with semicolon(;)
 x = 4; x=3; print(x + y)

One Statement in  Mutiple Lines
there cases where you write a single statement in multiple lines.q

fruits = ["orange","mango","banana",]
print(fruits)


